Oliver Tambo has been remembered as a builder of the ANC. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa says those who want to divide the ANC must go. Ramaphosa delivered the keynote address at the Oliver Tambo commemoration in Soweto and is taking the battle to his detractors in the ANC. A firm and straight-talking Ramaphosa says unity in the governing party ANC is not negotiable. The president says the ANC today is faced with the same challenges the party faced five decades ago, which prompted the Hani Memorandum. IN PICTURES: Remembering Oliver Tambo Ramaphosa says the ANC must move away from protecting the interests of individuals. "We should no longer be prepared to defend the indefensible," Ramaphosa said. "We have for long-closed ranks and divided working things being done. We can't do that anymore, accountability must he the order of the day " Ramaphosa says the ANC’s 2017 Nasrec Conference can be equated to the Morogoro Conference, which was also a turning point for the party.